iew%20of%20studies%20published%20in%20the%20journal%20Neuroscience%20and%20Biobehavioral%20Reviews%20found%20that%20lion's%20mane%20and%20other%20mushrooms%20could%20reduce%20anxiety%2C%20improve%20mood%2C%20and%20improve%20cognitive%20functioning.%20The%20researchers%20noted%20that%20more%20research%20needs%20to%20be%20done%20to%20confirm%20these%20findings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225977%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Coffee%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F663694e3ec0c696569011bec%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223990%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAlam%20adds%20lion's%20mane%20to%20his%20coffee.%3Cp%3EMichelle%20Lee%20Photography%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22c49e6671-7d73-4327-a6e7-6b9b190a5223%5C%22%3EZinc%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAlam%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhealth%2Fdiet-nutrition%2Fzinc-benefits%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etakes%20zinc%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20hope%20it%20might%20make%20him%20less%20sick%20when%20he's%20exposed%20to%20bugs%20from%20patients.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BZinc%20doesn't%20stop%20you%20from%20picking%20up%20a%20bug%2C%20but%20it%20does%20reduce%20how%20bad%20the%20bug%20or%20the%20infection%20could%20be%20when%20you%20do%20get%20it.%20So%20it%20might%20reduce%20the%20length%20of%20time%20that%20you're%20feeling%20unwell%2C%20or%20it%20might%20reduce%20the%20delays%20in%20your%20recovery%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%202022%20review%20of%20studies%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Epublished%20in%20the%20journal%20Nutrients%20found%20zinc%20appeared%20to%20shorten%20the%20duration%20of%20colds%20and%20lessen%20symptoms%2C%20but%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fods.od.nih.gov%2Ffactsheets%2FZinc-HealthProfessional%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emore%20research%20is%20needed%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMost%20people%20in%20the%20US%20get%20enough%20zinc%20from%20their%20diets%2C%20according%20to%20the%20Office%20of%20Dietary%20Supplements%2C%20but%20Alam%20thinks%20taking%20zinc%20supplements%20is%20%26quot%3Bworth%20a%20try%26quot%3B%20because%20most%20doses%20of%20zinc%20from%20shop-bought%20supplements%20%26quot%3Baren't%20going%20to%20cause%20any%20harm.%26quot%3B%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20important%20to%20note%2C%20though%2C%20that%20taking%20too%20much%20zinc%20(more%20than%2040%20milligrams%20a%20day%20for%20adults)%20can%20lead%20to%20nausea%2C%20dizziness%2C%20headaches%2C%20an%20upset%20stomach%2C%20vomiting%2C%20and%20loss%20of%20appetite%2C%20according%20to%20the%20Office%20of%20Dietary%20Supplements.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%223d762adc-f729-4e07-a6d2-8450f36a6155%5C%22%3EVitamin%20D%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EFrom%20September%20to%20whenever%20the%20weather%20improves%20in%20the%20spring%2C%20Alam%20also%20supplements%20his%20diet%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhealth%2Fdiet-nutrition%2Fhow-much-vitamin-d-should-i-take%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Evitamin%20D%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20is%20necessary%20for%20bone%20health%2C%20calcium%20absorption%20in%20the%20gut%2C%20reducing%20inflammation%2C%20and%20immune%20function%2C%20according%20to%20the%20US%20Office%20of%20Dietary%20Supplements.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BResearch%20says%20if%20you%20were%20to%20test%20every%20person%20in%20the%20UK%20at%20the%20end%20of%20a%20long%20winter%2C%20probably%2040%25%20of%20us%20would%20be%20vitamin%20D%20deficient.%20Especially%20with%20our%20lifestyles%20nowadays%20as%20we're%20more%20indoors%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20In%20the%20US%2C%20about%2035%25%20of%20adults%20have%20vitamin%20D%20deficiency%2C%20according%20to%20Cleveland%20Clinic.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGuidelines%20on%20supplementation%20are%20different%20around%20the%20world.%20For%20example%2C%20the%20UK%20government%20advises%20people%20to%20consider%20taking%20vitamin%20D%20during%20the%20fall%20and%20winter%2C%20whereas%20The%20Endocrine%20Society%20doesn't%20recommend%20vitamin%20D%20supplementation%20for%20healthy%20adults%20aged%2019%20to%2074%2C%20because%20research%20doesn't%20suggest%20a%20clear%20amount%20which%20is%20effective%20for%20preventing%20disease.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20up%20to%20the%20individual%20to%20decide%20whether%20to%20take%20vitamin%20D%20supplements%2C%20but%2C%20like%20zinc%2C%20they%20are%20unlikely%20to%20cause%20harm%20when%20taken%20in%20safe%20amounts%2C%20Alam%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdoctor-supplement-energy-recovery-sick-2024-8%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1724494982000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66b6039f5da406397bf46ea3%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdoctor-supplement-energy-recovery-sick-2024-8%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20doctor%20takes%20supplements%20to%20help%20him%20cut%20down%20on%20coffee%20and%20recover%20faster%20when%20he's%20sick.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22skenny%40businessinsider.com%20(Serafina%20Kenny)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdoctor-supplement-energy-recovery-sick-2024-8%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Working%20for%20Doordash%20and%20Grubhub%20increasingly%20feels%20like%20a%209-5.%20And%20that%20may%20be%20bad%20news%20for%20the%20companies.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221208%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20DoorDash%20driver%20in%20car%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65450a813cc84b4dfafbcf80%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221080%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EGig%20delivery%20workers%20are%20independent%20contractors%2C%20but%20some%20say%20their%20work%20looks%20more%20like%20that%20of%20employees%20at%20times.%3Cp%3EDoorDash%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EWorkers%20say%20elements%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgolden-age-gig-work-instacart-doordash-delivery-jobs-over-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egig%20delivery%3C%2Fa%3E%20conflict%20with%20the%20flexible%20image%20companies%20use%20to%20promote%20it.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThey%20often%20have%20to%20take%20shifts%20or%20hit%20a%20minimum%20acceptance%20rate%20to%20access%20the%20best-paying%20orders.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EWorkers%20say%20parts%20of%20gig%20delivery%20don't%20fit%20the%20independent%20contractor%20mold.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20weekends%2C%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgolden-age-gig-work-instacart-doordash-delivery-jobs-over-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egig%20delivery%20worker%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20Utah%20takes%20out%20his%20phone%20and%20opens%20one%20of%20three%20apps%20to%20make%20some%20extra%20money%20as%20an%20independent%20contractor.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20working%20on%20apps%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-delivery-driver-gets-big-tips-declines-orders-wealthy-areas-2023-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDoorDash%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Uber%20Eats%2C%20and%20Grubhub%20doesn't%20always%20feel%20as%20independent%20as%20the%20term%20suggests%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EApps%20from%20Instacart%20to%20Uber%20often%20tout%20flexibility%20as%20a%20key%20benefit%20of%20working%20for%20them.%20Unlike%20W2%20workers%2C%20they%20say%2C%20independent%20contractors%20can%20take%20the%20gigs%20that%20work%20for%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20people%20doing%20the%20work%20say%20that%20things%20like%20performance%20metrics%20often%20eat%20into%20that%20flexibility.%20The%20end%20result%3A%20Jobs%20that%20pay%20like%20gigs%20but%20with%20demands%20that%20most%20workers%20would%20associate%20with%209-to-5s.%20And%20that's%20causing%20dissatisfaction%20among%20some%20workers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20example%20is%20DoorDash's%20%26quot%3Bacceptance%20rate%26quot%3B%20metric.%20While%20on%20the%20app%2C%20DoorDash%20sends%20the%20Utah%20worker%20orders%20that%20he%20could%20deliver%2C%20including%20details%20on%20how%20far%20he'd%20have%20to%20drive%20and%20how%20much%20the%20gig%20would%20pay%20if%20he%20accepted%20it.%20He%20can%20turn%20it%20down%2C%20but%20that%20drags%20down%20his%20acceptance%20rate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20it%20falls%20below%2050%25%2C%20DoorDash%20offers%20him%20fewer%20of%20the%20top-paying%20ones.%20The%20requirement%20is%20one%20of%20multiple%20metrics%20workers%20need%20to%20meet%20to%20be%20part%20of%20DoorDash's%20Dasher%20Rewards%20program%2C%20which%20can%20give%20gig%20workers%20access%20%26quot%3Bto%20high-paying%20orders%26quot%3B%20and%20flexibility%20on%20when%20they%20work%2C%20DoorDash%20says%20on%20its%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fhelp.doordash.com%2Fdashers%2Fs%2Farticle%2FDasher-Rewards-Program-Pilot%3Flanguage%3Den_US%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewebsite%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20doesn't%20feel%20much%20like%20I'm%20on%20contract%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20Utah%20gig%20worker%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BYou%20can't%20Doordash%20whenever%20you%20want%20to%20unless%20you're%20at%20the%20top%20Platinum%20Tier.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20DoorDash%20spokesperson%20said%20it%20is%20%26quot%3Bblatantly%20inaccurate%26quot%3B%20to%20say%20that%20the%20company%20counts%20orders%20that%20its%20contractors%20don't%20take%20against%20them.%20Still%2C%20the%20spokesperson%20confirmed%20that%20DoorDash%20does%20require%20its%20workers%20to%20maintain%20an%20acceptance%20rate%20of%20at%20least%2050%25%20to%20participate%20in%20its%20Dasher%20Rewards%20program%20in%20most%20places%20where%20it%20operates.%20Other%20factors%2C%20such%20as%20customer%20ratings%2C%20also%20matter%20for%20the%20program.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTo%20be%20extremely%20clear%2C%20every%20single%20Dasher%20has%20the%20freedom%20to%20accept%20or%20decline%20as%20many%20offers%20as%20they%20choose%2C%20and%20they're%20never%20penalized%20based%20on%20their%20acceptance%20rate%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20spokesperson%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20metrics%20such%20as%20this%20are%20just%20one%20aspect%20of%20delivery%20gig%20work%20that%20workers%20say%20feels%20like%20a%20traditional%20job.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20one%20Chicago%20delivery%20worker%20told%20BI%20that%20he%20avoids%20Grubhub%20due%20to%20the%20app's%20scheduling%20feature.%20The%20feature%20asks%20workers%20to%20sign%20up%20to%20deliver%20during%20specific%20shifts%2C%20which%20can%20range%20from%2030%20minutes%20to%20a%20few%20hours.%20Grubhub%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment%20from%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20workers%20don't%20have%20to%20sign%20up%20for%20blocks%20to%20deliver%20for%20Grubhub%20%E2%80%94%20the%20app%20also%20offers%20the%20option%20to%20take%20one-off%20orders%20%E2%80%94%20the%20company%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdriver.grubhub.com%2Fdriver-scheduling%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3DGrubhub%2520delivery%2520partners%2520don%2527t%2Cto%2520earn%2520when%2520they%2520want.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etells%20its%20contractors%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20%26quot%3Bscheduling%20blocks%20is%20the%20best%20way%20to%20maximize%20orders%20and%20support%20earnings.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInstead%2C%20the%20Chicago%20delivery%20worker%20said%20he%20prefers%20Uber%20Eats%20since%20the%20app%20allows%20workers%20to%20%26quot%3Bwork%20whenever%20you%20want%2C%20wherever%20you%20want.%26quot%3B%20He%20added%20that%20the%20downsides%20of%20having%20a%20low%20acceptance%20rate%20and%20customer%20ratings%20%26quot%3Baren't%20as%20harsh%20as%20the%20other%20apps.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOther%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwalmart-spark-drivers-over-hour-waiting-orders-in-parking-lots-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egig%20workers%20say%20they%20spend%20unpaid%20hours%20waiting%20in%20a%20parking%20lot%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20stores%20like%20Costco%20and%20Walmart%20just%20to%20claim%20orders%20%E2%80%94%20a%20habit%20that%20they%20say%20feels%20more%20like%20clocking%20into%20a%20regular%20job%20than%20working%20on%20their%20own%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20delivery%20apps%20such%20as%20Instacart%20and%20Walmart's%20Spark%20give%20workers%20who%20are%20near%20a%20store%20better%20access%20to%20orders%2C%20incentivizing%20workers%20to%20show%20up%20during%20the%20busiest%20times%20of%20day%20in%20hopes%20of%20claiming%20an%20order.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20recent%20laws%20have%20attempted%20to%20clarify%20what%20companies%20can%20ask%20of%20gig%20workers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESeattle's%20PayUp%20law%20for%20gig%20delivery%20workers%2C%20which%20took%20effect%20in%20January%2C%20forbids%20delivery%20companies%20from%20retaliating%20against%20workers%20who%20limit%20their%20availability%20or%20reject%20orders%20they%20believe%20aren't%20worth%20the%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20companies%20also%20have%20to%20provide%20gig%20workers%20with%20details%20about%20pay%20and%20what%20filling%20the%20order%20will%20involve%2C%20such%20as%20how%20long%20the%20order%20will%20take%20to%20deliver%2C%20before%20the%20gig%20work%20accepts%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNow%2C%20in%20Seattle%2C%20we%20are%20truly%20independent%20contractors%2C%26quot%3B%20one%20gig%20delivery%20worker%20who%20works%20in%20the%20Seattle%20area%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeantime%20in%20April%2C%20the%20US%20Department%20of%20Labor%20implemented%20a%20new%20rule%20that%20distinguishes%20between%20employee%20jobs%20and%20work%20done%20by%20independent%20contractors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20rule%20points%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dol.gov%2Fagencies%2Fwhd%2Fflsa%2Fmisclassification%2Frulemaking%2Ffaqs%23%3A~%3Atext%3DUnder%2520the%2520final%2520rule%252C%2520the%2Cno%2520one%2520factor%2520is%2520determinative.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esix%20factors%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20employers%20can%20use%20to%20determine%20which%20category%20a%20worker%20falls%20into%2C%20such%20as%20whether%20the%20worker%20can%20decline%20jobs%20and%20whether%20the%20employer%20sets%20a%20worker's%20schedule.%20It%20also%20replaced%20a%20Trump-era%20rule%20that%20considered%20just%20two%20factors%20and%20was%20more%20favorable%20to%20employers%2C%20David%20Jacobs%2C%20an%20adjunct%20professor%20at%20American%20University's%20Kogod%20School%20of%20Business%2C%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGig%20delivery%20companies%20such%20as%20DoorDash%20and%20Instacart%20told%20BI%20earlier%20this%20year%20that%20they%20weren't%20planning%20to%20change%20how%20they%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finstacart-doordash-uber-federal-rule-wont-change-gig-workers-status-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eclassify%20their%20independent%20contractors%3C%2Fa%3E%20based%20on%20the%20rule.%20One%20legal%20expert%20told%20The%20Wall%20Street%20Journal%20at%20the%20time%20that%20it%20would%20likely%20face%20tests%20in%20court%20through%20disputes%20between%20contractors%20and%20companies%20over%20whether%20they%20should%20be%20classified%20as%20employees.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJacobs%20said%20the%20rule%20is%20just%20one%20example%20of%20the%20broader%20conflict%20between%20gig%20workers%20and%20the%20companies%20they%20work%20for%20over%20how%20their%20jobs%20should%20be%20categorized.%20For%20many%20gig%20workers%20and%20their%20supporters%2C%20%26quot%3Bthere%20obviously%20is%20a%20desire%20to%20convert%20jobs%20to%20more%20traditional%20mutual%20obligation%20jobs%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%20%E2%80%94%20aka%20roles%20that%20might%20require%20more%20benefits.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20on%20the%20companies'%20side%2C%20there's%20a%20great%20deal%20of%20focus%20on%20the%20other%20model%2C%20%26quot%3Bwhich%20is%20to%20maintain%20flexibility%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EDo%20you%20work%20for%20a%20gig%20delivery%20service%20and%20have%20a%20story%20idea%20to%20share%3F%20Reach%20out%20to%20this%20reporter%20at%20abitter%40businessinsider.com%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdoordash-grubhub-uber-workers-gig-work-feels-like-a-job-2024-8%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1724494682000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65450b0eb788914e554fabec%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdoordash-grubhub-uber-workers-gig-work-feels-like-a-job-2024-8%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Gig%20delivery%20workers%20for%20apps%20like%20DoorDash%20and%20Uber%20Eats%20say%20being%20an%20independent%20contractor%20isn't%20as%20freeing%20as%20promised.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22abitter%40businessinsider.com%20(Alex%20Bitter)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdoordash-grubhub-uber-workers-gig-work-feels-like-a-job-2024-8%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Instead%20of%20spending%20money%20on%20camp%20or%20day%20care%2C%20I%20kept%20my%20daughter%20home%20this%20summer.%20We%20got%20more%20quality%20time%2C%20but%20it%20was%20harder%20to%20work.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223816%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20author%20and%20his%20daughter%20standing%20outside%20in%20front%20of%20an%20Amtrak%20train%20and%20smiling.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66c73dc11aa2ac29ee333d0b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222862%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20author%20got%20to%20spend%20more%20quality%20time%20with%20his%20daughter%20this%20summer.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Evan%20Porter%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EThis%20summer%2C%20instead%20of%20sending%20our%20oldest%20to%20summe