e%20past%20decade-plus%2C%20significant%20gaps%20remain%20between%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fblack-workers-lost-jobs-pandemic-still-look-work-recovery-uneven-2022-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eemployment%20rates%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20Black%20men%20and%20white%2C%20Asian%2C%20and%20Hispanic%2FLatino%20men%20between%20ages%2025%20and%2054.%20As%20of%20July%2C%20each%20of%20those%20three%20groups%20had%20working%20rates%20above%2087%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FP6oHd%2F1%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Prime-age%20employment-population%20ratio%20for%20men%20by%20race%2Fethnicity%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22514%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3ESecond%2C%20the%20true%20picture%20of%20Black%20male%20employment%20could%20be%20worse%20than%20the%20BLS's%20data%20suggests%2C%20Harry%20Holzer%2C%20a%20labor%20economist%20at%20Georgetown%20University%20and%20former%20chief%20economist%20at%20the%20US%20Department%20of%20Labor%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20That's%20because%20a%20significant%20number%20of%20Black%20men%20aren't%20being%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.brookings.edu%2Farticles%2Fwhy-are-employment-rates-so-low-among-black-men%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaccounted%20for%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20employment%20surveys.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20the%20BLS%20calculates%20employment%20rates%2C%20it%20only%20looks%20at%20Americans%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bls.gov%2Fcps%2Fdefinitions.htm%23%3A~%3Atext%3DEmployment%252Dpopulation%2520ratio%2C-The%2520employment%252Dpopulation%26amp%3Btext%3DIn%2520other%2520words%252C%2520it%2520is%2CCivilian%2520Noninstitutional%2520Population)%2520x%2520100%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaged%3C%2Fa%3E%2016%20and%20older%20who%20aren't%20in%20institutions%20like%20prisons%20or%20active%20duty%20in%20the%20military.%20That%20means%20that%20the%20tens%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bop.gov%2Fabout%2Fstatistics%2Fstatistics_inmate_race.jsp%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethousands%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20Black%20men%20who%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstudy-finds-huge-racial-disparity-in-americas-prisons-2016-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eincarcerated%3C%2Fa%3E%20aren't%20being%20included%20in%20these%20calculations%2C%20effectively%20boosting%20the%20Black%20male%20employment%20rate.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EAs%20of%202017%2C%20Black%20people%20accounted%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pewresearch.org%2Fshort-reads%2F2019%2F04%2F30%2Fshrinking-gap-between-number-of-blacks-and-whites-in-prison%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E12%25%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20the%20US%20population%20but%2033%25%20of%20the%20prison%20population%2C%20according%20to%20a%20Pew%20Research%20analysis.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAdditionally%2C%20Holzer%20said%20it's%20likely%20that%20some%20Black%20men%20who%20aren't%20incarcerated%20or%20in%20the%20military%20aren't%20getting%20picked%20up%20in%20these%20household%20surveys%2C%20perhaps%20because%20they're%20%26quot%3Bnot%20officially%20part%20of%20any%20household%2C%20though%20they%20might%20cohabit%20with%20family%20or%20significant%20others%20for%20periods%20of%20time.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20of%20July%2C%20the%20BLS%20estimated%20a%20there%20were%2016.2%20million%20US%20Black%20men%20in%20the%20noninstitutional%20population%2C%20compared%20to%2018.8%20million%20Black%20women.%20Other%20cohorts%20tend%20to%20have%20a%20significantly%20lower%20gender%20disparity%2C%20Holzer%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20bottom%20line%3A%20If%20the%20survey%20data%20had%20a%20more%20complete%20picture%20of%20Black%20men%2C%20Holzer%20said%20the%20Black%20male%20employment%20rate%20would%20likely%20be%20%26quot%3Bconsiderably%20worse.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHaving%20these%20men%20be%20missing%20makes%20the%20numbers%20look%20even%20better%20than%20they%20really%20are%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%20of%20the%20Black%20male%20employment%20rate%2C%20adding%2C%20%26quot%3BWe%20have%20every%20reason%20to%20believe%20that%20if%20we%20were%20counting%20them%2C%20the%20employment%20rate%20would%20be%20lower.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-men-working-less-recessions-employment-productivity-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estory%20of%20working%20men%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20US%20is%20a%20complicated%20one.%20Collectively%2C%20men%20between%20the%20ages%20of%2025%20and%2054%20are%20working%20at%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-men-working-less-recessions-employment-productivity-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esignificantly%20lower%20rate%3C%2Fa%3E%20than%20they%20did%20in%20the%201950s%20%E2%80%94%20but%20at%20nearly%20the%20highest%20rate%20in%20the%20last%2015%20years.%20When%20zooming%20in%20on%20Black%20men%2C%20there's%20another%20complicated%20story.%20While%20the%20share%20of%20working%20Black%20men%20is%20higher%20than%20it%20was%20a%20decade%20ago%2C%20there%20are%20still%20many%20of%20them%20who%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fblack-history-month-charts-black-americans-progress-inequality-2021-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecan't%20find%20jobs%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20have%20given%20up%20looking%20%E2%80%94%20and%20the%20employment%20gap%20between%20other%20groups%20persists.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20Black%20women%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fblog.dol.gov%2F2021%2F08%2F03%2F5-facts-about-black-women-in-the-labor-force%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emore%20likely%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20be%20working%20than%20white%2C%20Asian%2C%20or%20Hispanic%2FLatino%20women%2C%20which%20suggests%20Black%20men%20could%20face%20a%20unique%20set%20of%20challenges%20in%20the%20labor%20market%2C%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EValerie%20Wilson%2C%20a%20labor%20economist%20and%20the%20director%20of%20the%20Economic%20Policy%20Institute's%20program%20on%20race%2C%20ethnicity%2C%20and%20the%20economy%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHolzer%20and%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EWilson%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eshared%20why%20the%20employment%20gap%20between%20Black%20men%20and%20other%20groups%20persists%2C%20what's%20driven%20progress%20in%20recent%20years%2C%20and%20what%20else%20can%20be%20done%20in%20the%20years%20to%20come.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22828caa01-f6c0-4138-abd4-264997cfa5f1%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EEducation%20differences%20and%20discrimination%20can%20work%20against%20Black%20men%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EEducation%20is%20one%20factor%20that%20can%20help%20explain%20the%20lower%20employment%20rate%20of%20Black%20men%2C%20Wilson%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGenerally%2C%20people%20with%20higher%20levels%20of%20education%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bls.gov%2Femp%2Fchart-unemployment-earnings-education.htm%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eless%20likely%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20be%20unemployed%2C%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eand%20Black%20men%20have%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.census.gov%2Fdata%2Ftables%2Ftime-series%2Fdemo%2Feducational-attainment%2Fcps-historical-time-series.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elower%3C%2Fa%3E%20high%20school%20and%20college%20graduation%20rates%20than%20white%20and%20Asian%20men.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20Wilson%20said%20that%20education%20doesn't%20tell%20the%20whole%20story.%20For%20example%2C%20Black%20Americans%20have%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.americanprogress.org%2Farticle%2Fafrican-americans-face-systematic-obstacles-getting-good-jobs%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehigher%3C%2Fa%3E%20unemployment%20rates%20than%20white%20Americans%20even%20when%20they%20have%20the%20same%20level%20of%20education.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPart%20of%20the%20reason%20why%20these%20racial%20disparities%20are%20so%20persistent%20is%20because%20there%20is%20discrimination%20in%20the%20labor%20market%2C%20and%20the%20disparity%20doesn't%20get%20erased%20by%20accounting%20for%20factors%20such%20as%20education%20or%20experience%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20discrimination%20can%20come%20early%20in%20the%20hiring%20process.%20A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fbfi.uchicago.edu%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F04%2FBFI_WP_2024-40.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eworking%20paper%3C%2Fa%3E%20published%20in%20April%20by%20researchers%20at%20the%20University%20of%20California%2C%20Berkeley%20and%20the%20University%20of%20Chicago%20found%20that%20companies%20were%20up%20to%2024%25%20more%20likely%20to%20call%20back%20applicants%20with%20a%20%26quot%3Bdistinctively%20white%20name%26quot%3B%20than%20those%20with%20a%20%26quot%3Bdistinctively%20Black%20name.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJared%2C%20a%20Black%20man%20in%20his%2030s%20who%20was%20laid%20off%20from%20his%20data%20scientist%20job%20over%20a%20year%20ago%2C%20told%20BI%20he's%20struggled%20to%20find%20work%20in%20his%20industry.%20He%20thinks%20there%20are%20several%20reasons%20his%20search%20has%20been%20challenging%2C%20but%20he%20believes%20discrimination%20has%20played%20a%20role.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBetween%20finance%20and%20tech%2C%20most%20of%20my%20interviewers%20are%20Asian%20or%20white%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20adding%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20do%20feel%20like%20there%20are%20a%20lot%20of%20prejudices%20working%20against%20me%20but%20there's%20nothing%20I%20can%20do%20to%20change%20the%20way%20the%20world%20works.%26quot%3B%20Jared's%20identity%20is%20known%20to%20BI%2C%20but%20a%20pseudonym%20was%20used%20due%20to%20his%20concerns%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eabout%20professional%20repercussions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20when%20Black%20and%20white%20men%20are%20raised%20in%20homes%20with%20the%20same%20income%20and%20number%20of%20parents%2C%20Black%20men%20go%20on%20to%20earn%20significantly%20less%20on%20average%2C%20according%20to%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fopportunityinsights.org%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2018%2F04%2Frace_paper.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estudy%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20Harvard%20and%20Stanford%20researchers%20published%20in%202018.%20The%20study's%20authors%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2Finteractive%2F2018%2F03%2F19%2Fupshot%2Frace-class-white-and-black-men.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edidn't%20find%3C%2Fa%3E%20a%20meaningful%20earnings%20gap%20between%20Black%20and%20white%20women%20raised%20in%20similar%20households%2C%20which%20they%20said%20suggested%20Black%20men%20face%20a%20different%20set%20of%20challenges%20than%20Black%20women%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20entering%20the%20workforce.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22d440f4c4-540e-4048-b58e-210f2c41c7ed%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EIncarceration%20and%20a%20lack%20of%20workforce%20connections%20can%20create%20additional%20obstacles%20to%20employment%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EHigh%20incarceration%20rates%20among%20Black%20men%20aren't%20just%20a%20factor%20that%20makes%20their%20employment%20rate%20look%20rosier%20than%20the%20reality.%20Having%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fformerly-incarcerated-people-employment-recruiting-2022-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecriminal%20record%3C%2Fa%3E%20can%20make%20it%20considerably%20harder%20for%20Black%20men%20to%20find%20jobs%20once%20they%20return%20to%20society%2C%20Wilson%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.prisonpolicy.org%2Fblog%2F2022%2F02%2F08%2Femployment%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3DThe%2520struggle%2520to%2520find%2520a%2520good%2520job%26amp%3Btext%3DThe%2520average%2520working%2520person%2520is%2C%252C%2520construction%252C%2520and%2520food%2520service.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eanalysis%3C%2Fa%3E%20published%20in%202022%20by%20the%20Prison%20Policy%20Initiative%2C%20a%20think%20tank%2C%20found%20that%20nearly%20two-thirds%20of%20roughly%2050%2C000%20Americans%20released%20from%20federal%20prison%20in%202010%20weren't%20employed%20four%20years%20later.%20The%20analysis%20didn't%20focus%20specifically%20on%20Black%20Americans%2C%20but%20among%20the%20formerly%20incarcerated%20who%20found%20employment%2C%20Black%20and%20Native%20American%20men%20had%20the%20lowest%20earnings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20addition%20to%20discrimination%2C%20the%20impacts%20of%20incarceration%2C%20and%20lower%20levels%20of%20education%2C%20Holzer%20pointed%20to%20a%20few%20other%20factors%20working%20against%20some%20Black%20men.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20lack%20of%20work%20experience%20early%20in%20life%20can%20make%20it%20difficult%20for%20some%20Black%20men%20to%20land%20jobs%20down%20the%20road%2C%20he%20said.%20Additionally%2C%20some%20young%20Black%20men%20don't%20have%20enough%20role%20models%20and%20connections%20in%20the%20workforce.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20there's%20a%20lot%20of%20young%20Black%20men%20coming%20up%20who%20don't%20know%20that%20many%20older%20Black%20men%20who%20are%20working%20in%20good%20jobs%20in%20their%20families%20and%20in%20their%20neighborhoods%2C%26quot%3B%20Holzer%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAdditionally%2C%20Holzer%20said%20various%20factors%2C%20including%20health%20issues%2C%20disabilities%2C%20and%20not%20being%20married%20or%20having%20custody%20of%20children%2C%20could%20lead%20to%20Black%20men%20having%20less%20capability%20or%20motivation%20to%20work%20%E2%80%94%20these%20factors%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-men-working-less-recessions-employment-productivity-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ealso%20impact%3C%2Fa%3E%20white%2C%20Asian%2C%20and%20Hispanic%2FLatino%20men.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%222224d789-28b0-473d-b275-3aa3d5af699b%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20strong%20job%20market%20and%20workforce%20development%20programs%20could%20drive%20progress%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20several%20things%20that%20might%20help%20get%20more%20Black%20men%20into%20the%20workforce.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBoth%20Holzer%20and%20Wilson%20said%20the%20tight%20labor%20market%20of%20recent%20years%20%E2%80%94%20which%20included%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjolts-july-job-openings-labor-market-worker-shortage-hiring-data-2021-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erecord%20levels%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20job%20openings%20%E2%80%94%20was%20arguably%20the%20top%20reason%20the%20Black%20employment%20rate%20improved.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BA%20lot%20of%20employers%20just%20couldn't%20find%20the%20people%20whom%20they%20were%20used%20to%20finding%2C%26quot%3B%20Holzer%20said.%20%26quot%3BWhen%20that%20happens%2C%20employers%20all%20of%20a%20sudden%20are%20more%20open%20to%20hiring%20from%20groups%20whom%20historically%20they've%20shunned.%20And%20I%20think%20a%20lot%20of%20Black%20men%20are%20in%20that%20category.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjobs-report-labor-market-hiring-layoffs-quits-recession-sahm-rule-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ejob%20market%20has%20slowed%3C%2Fa%3E%20over%20the%20past%20year%2C%20Wilson%20said%20the%20Federal%20Reserve's%20decisions%20regarding%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finterest-rate-cuts-timeline-federal-reserve-inflation-powell-economists-forecast-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Einterest%20rates%3C%2Fa%3E%20will%20play%20an%20important%20role%20in%20ensuring%20a%20slowdown%20doesn't%20turn%20into%20something%20worse%20%E2%80%94%20making%20the%20job%20market%20tougher%20for%20all%20Americans.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20boost%20Black%20male%20employment%2C%20Holzer%20and%20Wilson%20said%20policymakers%20and%20communities%20could%20foc