e%20operations%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20a%20new%20frontier%20that%20can%20determine%20the%20course%20of%20war.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESpace-based%20technology%20has%20long%20given%20the%20US%20military%20an%20edge.%20It%20can%20track%20the%20movements%20of%20enemy%20weapons%20with%20powerful%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmanned-orbiting-laboratory-crewed-us-spy-satellite-never-sent-to-space-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Espy%20lenses%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20provide%20the%20navigation%20and%20communications%20systems%20ships%2C%20aircraft%2C%20and%20troops%20in%20the%20field%20depend%20upon.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEnter%20the%20space%20plane.%20From%20one%20vantage%2C%20they%20could%20be%20robot%20keepers%20who%20keep%20these%20large%20networks%20fueled%20and%20functional%2C%20but%20from%20another%2C%20they%20could%20be%20orbiting%20spies%20and%20saboteurs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhat's%20clear%20is%20that%20their%20missions%20are%20getting%20more%20complex%2C%20as%20is%20their%20centrality%20to%20the%20strategies%20of%20the%20two%20countries%20that%20fly%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20uncrewed%20X-37B%2C%20seen%20here%20after%20its%202019%20landing%20at%20NASA's%20Kennedy%20Space%20Center%20Shuttle%20Landing%20Facility%2C%20is%20believed%20to%20be%20about%2030%20feet%20long.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66c3b57e1aa2ac29ee32576c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221333%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20uncrewed%20X-37B%2C%20seen%20here%20after%20its%202019%20landing%20at%20NASA's%20Kennedy%20Space%20Center%20Shuttle%20Landing%20Facility%2C%20is%20believed%20to%20be%20about%2030%20feet%20long.%3Cp%3EJeremy%20Webster%2FUS%20Air%20Force%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%223dc83e63-5cf2-42d5-8174-a6f3d2577c69%5C%22%3EX-37B%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EA%20space%20plane%20is%20a%20reusable%20spacefaring%20craft%20that%20can%20maneuver%20in%20space%20independently%20and%20also%20fly%20and%20glide%20within%20Earth's%20atmosphere.%20They%20are%20sent%20into%20space%20via%20a%20detachable%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musk-spacex-launch-secret-spy-satellites-space-force-government-2022-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erocket%20booster%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20contain%20a%20cargo%20bay%20to%20deploy%20satellites%20and%20other%20objects%20for%20use%20and%20experimentation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20completing%20their%20mission%2C%20they%20independently%20return%20to%20Earth's%20atmosphere%2C%20land%20at%20a%20designated%20landing%20site%20on%20their%20own%20power%2C%20and%20prepare%20for%20their%20next%20mission.%20The%20most%20well-known%20space%20planes%20are%20the%20American%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchallenger-video-nasa-space-shuttle-program-2016-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESpace%20Shuttle%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20the%20Soviet%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fairandspace.si.edu%2Fstories%2Feditorial%2Fsoviet-buran-shuttle-one-flight-long-history%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBuran%3C%2Fa%3E.%20But%20in%20contrast%20to%20the%20Space%20Shuttle%2C%20the%20X-37B%20is%20owned%20and%20operated%20by%20the%20military.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20X-37B's%20origin%20begins%20in%201999%2C%20when%20the%20civilian%20space%20agency%20NASA%20awarded%20Boeing%20a%20contract%20to%20develop%20a%20small%20unmanned%20spacecraft%20capable%20of%20fitting%20inside%20the%20Space%20Shuttle.%20What%20they%20created%20was%20a%20small%20space%20plane%20measuring%20approximately%2030%20feet%20long%20and%20with%20a%20wingspan%20of%2015%20feet%20%E2%80%94%20roughly%20one-fourth%20the%20size%20of%20the%20now-retired%20Space%20Shuttle.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20also%20contains%20a%20cargo%20bay%20measuring%20about%207%20feet%20by%204%20feet%2C%20which%2C%20in%20addition%20to%20housing%20satellites%20and%20other%20space%20cargo%20also%20holds%20a%20solar