n%202017.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66c3b6201aa2ac29ee3257c6%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221333%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20X-37B%20launched%20from%20NASA's%20Kennedy%20Space%20Center%20in%202017.%3Cp%3ESenior%20Airman%20Timothy%20Kirchner%2FUS%20Air%20Force%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20flight%20began%20on%20April%2022%2C%202010%2C%20and%20saw%20the%20first%20X-37B%20remain%20in%20orbit%20for%20a%20total%20of%20224%20days.%20The%20second%20flight%2C%20which%20was%20the%20second%20X-37B's%20inaugural%20mission%2C%20began%20on%20March%205%2C%202011%2C%20and%20was%20extended%20well%20beyond%20its%20original%20270-day%20limit%20to%20a%20total%20of%20468%20days.%20The%20third%20flight%2C%20beginning%20on%20December%2011%2C%202012%2C%20marked%20the%20first%20time%20an%20X-37B%20had%20been%20reused%2C%20and%20lasted%20674%20days.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20fourth%20flight%20began%20on%20May%2020%2C%202015.%20Over%20the%20course%20of%20717%20days%2C%20the%20space%20plane%20tested%20new%20propulsion%20technology%20for%20satellites%20as%20well%20as%20the%20effects%20of%20radiation%20on%20certain%20objects.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20X-37B's%20fifth%20flight%20on%20September%207%2C%202017%20was%20launched%20atop%20Space%20X's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.spacex.com%2Fvehicles%2Ffalcon-9%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFalcon%209%3C%2Fa%3E%20rocket%20(all%20previous%20launches%20were%20with%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ulalaunch.com%2Frockets%2Fatlas-v%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAtlas%20V%3C%2Fa%3E%20rocket).%20Over%20the%20course%20of%20780%20days%20%E2%80%94%20a%20little%20over%20two%20years%20%E2%80%94%20the%20space%20plane%20performed%20a%20number%20of%20activities%20and%20experiments%2C%20including%20the%20deployment%20of%20multiple%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.jpl.nasa.gov%2Ftopics%2Fcubesats%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECubeSat%3C%2Fa%3E%20satellites%2C%20which%20NASA%20foresees%20as%20an%20orbiting%20sensory%20network%20that%20can%20solve%20complex%20tasks%20with%20a%20%26quot%3Bpowerful%20central%20spacecraft.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20sixth%20flight%20began%20on%20May%2017%2C%202020%2C%20and%20lasted%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Funmanned-craft-us-space-force-lands-2-5-years-orbit-2022-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E908%20days%3C%2Fa%3E.%20It%20was%20the%20first%20mission%20conducted%20under%20the%20command%20of%20the%20newly%20formed%20U.S.%20Space%20Force%20and%20may%20have%20been%20one%20of%20the%20busiest%20missions%20yet.%20It%20exposed%20select%20materials%20to%20space%2C%20tested%20the%20effects%20of%20space%20radiation%20on%20seeds%2C%20and%20deployed%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.usafa.edu%2Fresearch%2Fresearch-centers%2Fspace-systems-research-center%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFalconSat-8%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20satellite%20built%20by%20US.%20Air%20Force%20Academy%20cadets%20to%20conduct%20five%20experiments.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20X-37B's%20most%20recent%20and%20current%20flight%20began%20on%20December%2028%2C%202023.%20Its%20mission%20is%20classified%2C%20with%20the%20Space%20Force%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.spaceforce.mil%2FNews%2FArticle-Display%2FArticle%2F3583347%2Fdepartment-of-the-air-force-scheduled-to-launch-seventh-x-37b-mission%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estating%3C%2Fa%3E%20only%20that%20it%20will%20be%20%26quot%3Boperating%20the%20reusable%20space%20plane%20in%20new%20orbital%20regimes%2C%20experimenting%20with%20future%20space%20domain%20awareness%20technologies%2C%20and%20investigating%20the%20radiation%20effects%20on%20materials%20provided%20by%20NASA.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fspace-force-guardian-nick-hague-spacex-rocket-iss-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESpace%20Force%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20not%20given%20the%20X-37B's%20flight%20path%2C%20but%20because%20it%20was%20launched%20atop%20SpaceX's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fphoto-spacex-falcon-heavy-launchpad-blasted-lightning-rocket-spaceflight-musk-2023-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFalcon%20Heavy%20rocket%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20there%20has%20been%20speculation%20that%20the%20space%20plane%20could%20be%20headed%20for%20a%20much%20higher%20orbit%20than%20previous%20missions%2C%20as%20the%20rocket%20is%20one%20of%20the%20most%20powerful%20in%20the%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20Long%20March-2F%20rocket%20blasted%20off%20in%20October%20carrying%20a%20manned%20spaceship%20from%20China's%20Jiuquan%20Satellite%20Launch%20Center.%20The%20Shenlong%20was%20launched%20on%20December%2014%20from%20the%20same%20center%20without%20images%20or%20fanfare.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66c4a4225da406397bf727df%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221333%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20Long%20March-2F%20rocket%20blasted%20off%20in%20October%20carrying%20a%20manned%20spaceship%20from%20China's%20Jiuquan%20Satellite%20Launch%20Center.%20The%20Shenlong%20was%20launched%20on%20December%2014%20from%20the%20same%20center%20without%20images%20or%20fanfare.%3Cp%3EWang%20Jiangbo%2FXinhua%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22ef23e953-67f4-4399-8bc9-c452d0019685%5C%22%3EShenlong%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ENamed%20after%20the%20most%20important%20dragon%20god%20in%20Chinese%20mythology%20and%20first%20revealed%20in%202007%2C%20the%20Shenlong%20is%20thought%20to%20be%20a%20direct%20Chinese%20response%20to%20the%20X-37B.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20program%20is%20surrounded%20in%20such%20extreme%20secrecy%20that%20there%20are%20no%20known%20images%20of%20the%20space%20plane%20in%20its%20current%20form.%20Images%20of%20what%20is%20believed%20to%20be%20a%20Shenlong%20