e%20months.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20X-37B%20launched%20on%20its%20sixth%20flight%20in%20May%202020%20from%20Cape%20Canaveral%20Air%20Force%20Station.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66c3b6df5da406397bf70740%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221280%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20X-37B%20launched%20on%20its%20sixth%20flight%20in%20May%202020%20from%20Cape%20Canaveral%20Air%20Force%20Station.%3Cp%3EPaul%20Hennessy%2FNurPhoto%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20addition%20to%20being%20considerably%20longer%2C%20the%20Shenlong's%20second%20flight%20was%20far%20more%20eventful.%20About%20two%20months%20into%20its%20flight%2C%20the%20space%20plane%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fspacenews.com%2Fchinas-spaceplane-conducted-proximity-and-capture-maneuvers-with-subsatellite-data-suggests%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edeployed%20a%20subsatellite%20and%20then%20practiced%20recovering%20it%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20least%20two%20(and%20possibly%20even%20three)%20times%2C%20a%20capability%20for%20so-called%20proximity%20operations%20that%20may%20allow%20it%20to%20snatch%20an%20enemy's%20satellite.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Shenlong%20embarked%20on%20its%20third%20and%20current%20flight%20on%20December%2014%2C%202023%2C%20just%20seven%20months%20after%20its%20second%20mission.%20In%20May%2C%20the%20Shenlong%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fspacenews.com%2Fchinas-secretive-spaceplane-conducts-proximity-operations-with-small-spacecraft%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereleased%20an%20object%20from%20its%20cargo%20hold%2C%20and%20began%20proximity%20operations%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20possibly%20even%20recapturing%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHow%20much%20longer%20the%20Shenlong%20will%20remain%20in%20orbit%2C%20as%20well%20as%20its%20future%20plans%20more%20broadly%2C%20remain%20secrets%20that%20the%20Chinese%20government%20has%20shown%20little%20appetite%20for%20divulging.%20The%20government%20has%20only%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fapp.xinhuanet.com%2Fnews%2Farticle.html%3FarticleId%3Db9141bb29a221c45ac2ad0d44dc87fc6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20space%20plane%20will%20eventually%20land%20in%20China%2C%20and%20that%20%26quot%3Breusable%20technology%20verification%20and%20space%20science%20experiments%20will%20be%20carried%20out%20as%20planned%20to%20provide%20technical%20support%20for%20the%20peaceful%20use%20of%20space.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20vague%20wording%20resembles%20previous%20statements%2C%20like%20those%20of%20its%20builder%2C%20China%20Aerospace%20Science%20and%20Technology%20Corporation%2C%20which%20has%20previously%20said%20that%20the%20Shenlong%20%26quot%3Bwill%20provide%20a%20more%20convenient%20and%20inexpensive%20way%20to%20access%20space%20for%20the%20peaceful%20use%20of%20space%20in%20the%20future.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221920%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20satellite%20networks%20of%20the%20US%20and%20its%20allies%20could%20be%20targeted%20by%20enemy%20spaceplanes.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66c3bda01aa2ac29ee3259df%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221280%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20satellite%20networks%20of%20the%20US%20and%20its%20allies%20could%20be%20targeted%20by%20enemy%20spaceplanes.%3Cp%3ENick%20Hague%2FNASA%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%222f25d6b5-fe78-4384-a750-e76f8663eacb%5C%22%3ESatellite%20threat%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EGiven%20the%20immense%20secrecy%20of%20the%20crafts%20and%20what%20is%20known%20about%20their%20capabilities%2C%20it's%20easy%20to%20understand%20speculation%20that%20the%20two%20space%20planes%20could%20be%20orbiting%20weapons%20platforms.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20very%20fact%20that%20the%20US%20Department%20of%20Defense%20is%20in%20charge%20of%20the%20X-37B%20instead%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcategory%2Fnasa%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENASA%3C%2Fa%3E%20confirms%20that%20the%20US%20government%20believes%20that%20there%20is%20a%20military%20application%20for%20the%20space%20plane.%20Similarly%2C%20the%20fact%20that%20the%20Chinese%20government%20has%20been%20so%20silent%20on%20the%20Shenlong's%20activities%20despite%20its%20penchant%20for%20boasting%20about%20its%20other%20space%20accomplishments%20may%20be%20a%20tacit%20indication%20that%20there%20is%20more%20to%20the%20Shenlong%20than%20the%20'peaceful%20use%20of%20space.'%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20most%20impactful%20possible%20uses%20of%20the%20space%20planes%20is%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-condemns-irresponsible-russian-anti-satellite-test-threatening-space-station-2021-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eanti-satellite%20assets%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Both%20have%20deployed%20satellites%20from%20their%20cargo%20bays%2C%20and%20the%20Shenlong's%20proximity%20operations%20may%20be%20training%20runs%20for%20attacks%20on%20hostile%20satellites%20in%20orbit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frussian-inspector-satellite-chasing-secret-us-military-satellite-cat-mouse-2023-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EProximity%20operations%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20murky.%20They%20could%20be%20dress%20rehearsals%20for%20disrupting%20or%20eavesdropping%20on%20an%20enemy's%20satellite%2C%20just%20as%20they%20could%20be%20drills%20for%20missions%20to%20refuel%20and%20repair%20one%20of%20the%20country's%20own%20satellites.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESatellites%20are%20among%20the%20most%20important%20assets%20for%20any%20first-rate%20military%2C%20as%20they%20are%20essential%20for%20secure%20communications%2C%20navigation%2C%20and%20intelligence%20gathering%20via%20orbital%20imaging%20and%20communication%20intercepts.%20They%20are%20even%20sometimes%20used%20to%20guide%20smart%20munitions%20to%20hostile%20targets%20as%20well.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENeutralizing%20an%20enemy's%20satellites%20would%20be%20one%20of%20the%20most%20important%20objectives%20in%20any%20potential%20conflict%20between%20the%20world's%20foremost%20military%20powers.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fswfound.org%2Fmedia%2F9550%2Fchinese_asat_fact_sheet_updated_2012.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EChina%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thespacereview.com%2Farticle%2F4198%2F1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EUS%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcarnegieendowment.org%2Fresearch%2F2019%2F04%2Findias-asat-test-an-incomplete-success%3Flang%3Den%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EIndia%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcarnegieendowment.org%2Fposts%2F2021%2F11%2Fthe-dangerous-fallout-of-russias-anti-satellite-missile-test%3Flang%3Den%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ERussia%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20each%20demonstrated%20a%20capability%20to%20destroy%20satellites%20in%20orbit%20with%20anti-satellite%20missiles%2C%20but%20each%20of%20those%20tests%20resulted%20in%20the%20creation%20of%20large%20debris%20fields%20in%20orbit%20that%20took%20sometimes%20took%20years%20to%20disappear.%20Such%20debris%20fields%20could%20also%20pose%20a%20very%20severe%20threat%20to%20friendly%20satellites%20as%20well.%20China's%20anti-satellite%20missile%20test%20in%202007%20triggered%20a%20space%20debris%20cloud%20that%20was%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fspectrum.ieee.org%2Fhollywood-space-disaster-gravity-uses-kessler-syndrome-for-scares%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Einspiration%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20the%20blockbuster%20film%20%26quot%3BGravity.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHaving%20a%20way%20to%20neutralize%20or%20even%20capture%20satellites%2C%20then%2C%20could%20be%20a%20better%20alternative.%20Tapping%20into%20enemy%20satellites%20to%20eavesdrop%20or%20shut%20down%20their%20data%20streams%20and%20communications%20could%20also%20serve%20as%20a%20better%20alternative%2C%20and%20may%20also%20be%20possible%20with%20the%20assistance%20of%20space%20plane%20(similar%20to%20the%20tapping%20of%20underwater%20cables%20by%20submarines).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20the%20militarization%20of%20space%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.csis.org%2Fanalysis%2Fthere-path-counter-russias-space-weapons%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eseemingly%20fast%20becoming%3C%2Fa%3E%20reality%20and%20with%20China's%20space%20program%20demonstrating%20that%20it%20can%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fspacenews.com%2Fchinas-shijian-21-spacecraft-docked-with-and-towed-a-dead-satellite%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etow%20away%20satellites%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20it%20is%20likely%20that%20space%20planes%20will%20only%20become%20more%20important%20in%20the%20years%20ahead.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EBenjamin%20Brimelow%20is%20a%20freelance%20journalist%20covering%20international%20military%20and%20defense%20issues.%20He%20holds%20a%20master's%20degree%20in%20Global%20Affairs%20with%20a%20concentration%20in%20international%20security%20from%20the%20Fletcher%20School%20of%20Law%20and%20Diplomacy.%20His%20work%20has%20appeared%20in%20Business%20Insider%20and%20the%20Modern%20War%20Institute%20at%20West%20Point.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fx-37b-vs-china-shenlong-space-plane-2024-8%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1724490002000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66c3b9e1b4912df3ae1cc874%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fx-37b-vs-china-shenlong-space-plane-2024-8%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20US%20X-37B%20and%20China's%20Shenlong%20are%20competing%20unmanned%20space%20planes%20whose%20covert%20missions%20are%20getting%20more%20complex.%20See%20how%20the%20spacecraft%20compare.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Benjamin%20Brimelow)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A92%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fx-37b-vs-china-shenlong-space-plane-2024-8%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22A%20famed%20economist%20who%20called%20the%202008%20recession%20warns%20the%20Fed%20is%20behind%20on%20rate%20cuts%20%E2%80%94%20and%20that%20a%20downturn%20is%20coming%20despite%20'off%20the%20charts'%20investor%20sentiment%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22stock%20trader%20panics%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5c887f51401d58071527f664%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EREUTERS%2FLucas%20Jackson%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EDavid%20Rosenberg%20warns%20of%20recession%20as%20labor-market%20revisions%20show%20818%2C000%20fewer%20jobs.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20Federal%20Reserve's%20rate%20hikes%20were%20based%20on%20overestimated%20job%20numbers%2C%20Rosenberg%20says.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EDespite%20recession%20risks%2C%20stocks%20are%20elevated%20as%20investors%20anticipate%20future%20rate%20cuts.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EMassive%20downward%20labor-market%20revisions%20are%20the%20latest%20sign%20that%20the%20US%20economy%20is%20heading%20toward%20a%20recession%20and%20the%20Federal%20Reserve%20is%20behind%20on%20interest%20rate%20cuts%2C%20according%20to%20the%20famed%20economist%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstock-market-crash-sp500-weak-breadth-recession-unemployment-rate-rosenberg-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDavid%20Rosenberg%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERosenberg%2C%20the%20founder%20of%20Rosenberg%20Research%20who%20called%20the%202008%20recession%20when%20he%20was%20chief%20economist%20for%20Merrill%20Lynch%2C%20pointed%20out%20in%20client%20notes%20this%20week%20that%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fstocks%2Feconomy-added-818000-fewer-jobs-ed-yardeni-says-dont-worry-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edownward%20revision%20to%20payrolls%20data%20by%20818%2C000%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20the%20March%202023-March%202024%20period%20is%20the%20largest%20since%20the%20Great%20Recession.%20That%20means%20trouble%20for%20the%20US%20economy%2C%20he%20believes%2C%20with%20the%20Fed%20having%20held%20rates%20in%20restrictive%20territory%20due%20to%20what%20it%20thought%20were%20stronger%20job%20numbers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIncredibly%2C%20the%20Fed%20raised%20rates%20500%20basis%20points%20under%20a%20false%20presumption%20%E2%80%94%20by%20over%20one%20million%20%E2%80%94%20of%20just%20how%20robust%20the%20jobs%20market%20was%2C%26quot%3B%20Rosenberg%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20added%20that%20Fed%20policy%20%26quot%3Bhas%20been%20too%20tight%2C%20and%20for%20too%20long%2C%20to%20avoid%20causing%20an%20economic%20slowdown.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20addition%20to%20the%20yearly%20revisions%2C%20monthly%20payroll%20revisions%20from%20the%20Bureau%20of%20Labor%20Statistics%20have%20also%20been%20poor%20more%20recently.%20Year-to-date%2C%20the%20number%20of%20jobs%20added%20has%20been%20revised%20down%20by%20a%20total%20of%20314%2C000%20jobs%2C%20and%20revisions%20have%20been%20negative%2075%25%20of%20months%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERosenberg%20has%20warned%20of%20a%20recession%20over%20the%20last%20couple%20of%20years%20as%20the%20Fed%20aggressively%20hiked%20rates%20to%20slow%20the%20economy%20and%20cool%20inflation%2C%20and%20is%20sticking%20to%20his%20call.%20In%20a%20note%20on%20Friday%2C%20he%20shared%20two%20recession%20indicators%20that%20he%20believes%20paint%20a%20worrying%20picture%20for%20the%20macro%20outlook%20going%20forward%20despite%20other%20recession%20signals%20like%20the%20Sahm%20Rule%20and%20the%20Treasury%20yield%20curve%20being%20called%20into%20question%20at%20the%20moment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20is%20a%20model%20that%20aims%20to%20enhance%20the%20yield%20curve%20as%20a%20recession%20indicator%20by%20taking%20into%20account%20US%20businesses'%20ability%20to%20repay%20debts%20and%20the%20Fed's%20National%20Financial%20Conditions%20Index.%20While%20the%20indicator%20is%20dropping%2C%20it%20has%20risen%20to%20levels%20only%20seen%20in%20prior%20recessions.%20In%20those%20instances%2C%20the%20economy%20was%20only%20in%20recession%20after%20the%20index%20started%20declining.%20The%20measure%20currently%20shows%20a%2057%25%20chance%20of%20a%20downturn.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221988%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22recession%20odds%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66c8f19dc72ebc54a40e8af8%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22988%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3ERosenberg%20Research%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20also%20included%20a%20new%20indicator%20from%20economists%20Pascal%20Michaillat%20and%20Emmanuel%20Saez%20that%20seeks%20to%20build%20on%20the%20Sahm%20Rule%20unemployment%20indicator%20by%20accounting%20for%20job%20openings%2C%20which%20signal%20businesses'%20appetite%20for%20hiring.%20The%20indicator%20is%20in%20%26quot%3Bpossible%20recession%26quot%3B%20territory%20and%20trending%20upward.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221666%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Michaillat%20and%20Saez%20Recession%20Indicator%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66c8ec811aa2ac29ee33e291%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221048%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3ERosenberg%20Research%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20the%20concerning%20data%2C%20stocks%20are%20just%20off%20all-time%20highs%2C%20valuations%20are%20historically%20elevated%2C%20and%20investors%20look%20forward%20to%20rate%20cuts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20smoothed%20CAPE%2C%20at%2035x%2C%20is%20double%20the%20long-run%20average%2C%26quot%3B%20Rosenberg%20said%2C%20referencing%20the%20Shiller%20cyclically-adjusted%20price-to-earnings%20ratio.%20%26quot%3BBe%20that%20as%20it%20may%2C%20there%20are%20the%20fundamentals%2C%20and%20then%20there%20are%20'animal%20spirits%2C'%20and%20sentiment%20over%20equities%20remains%20off%20the%20charts%20%E2%80%94%20the%20Market%20Vane%20bullish%20sentiment%2C%20at%2072%25%2C%20is%20back%20to%20where%20it%20was%20in%20January%202018%20(which%20in%20classic%20contrary%20fashion%2C%20presaged%20a%20very%20tough%20year%20for%20the%20risk-on%20trade)%20and%20before%20that%2C%20the%20spring%20of%202007%20(ahem)%20when%20Chuck%20Prince%20was%20telling%20the%20masses%20to%20keep%20on%20dancing%20(the%20music%20stopped%20not%20too%20long%20after).%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221626%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22market%20vane%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66c8ec4bc72ebc54a40e879c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221284%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3ERosenberg%20Research%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%228374ebd2-2999-4778-8d8c-9ce25338d116%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ERosenberg's%20views%20in%20context%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ENot%20every%20economist%20viewed%20the%20recent%20payroll%20revisions%20as%20negatively%20as%20Rosenberg.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIan%20Shepherdson%2C%20the%20chief%20economist%20at%20Pantheon%20Macroeconomics%2C%20said%20in%20a%20client%20note%20this%20week%20that%20the%20data%20is%20backward-looking%20and%20that%20average%20monthly%20job%20gains%20are%20still%20strong%20despite%20the%20revisions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20tells%20us%20nothing%20about%20payrolls%20since%20March%2C%20and%20has%20no%20implications%20for%20the%20unemployment%20rate%2C%20which%20is%20measured%20by%20the%20separate%20household%20survey%2C%26quot%3B%20Shepherdson%20said.%20%26quot%3BThe%20monthly%20profile%20of%20the%20benchmark%20revisions%20will%20be%20released%20next%20February%2C%20but%20the%20total%20roughly%20indicates%20that%20payrolls%20grew%20at%20a%20still-respectable%20average%20pace%20of%20about%20175K%20in%20the%20twelve%20months%20to%20March%2C%20compared%20to%20232K%20previously.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20soft-landing%20outcome%2C%20where%20the%20Fed%20avoids%20sending%20the%20economy%20into%20recession%2C%20is%20also%20still%20the%20consensus%20view%20on%20Wall%20Street.%20With%20inflation%20down%20under%203%25%20and%20rate%20cuts%20almost%20surely%20on%20the%20way%2C%20such%20a%20scenario%20is%20still%20seemingly%20possible.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20there's%20no%20question%20that%20recession%20risks%20are%20being%20taken%20more%20seriously%20following%20the%20payroll%20revisions%20and%20July's%20underwhelming%20jobs%20report%20%E2%80%94%20including%20by%20Fed%20Chair%20Jerome%20Powell.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20cooling%20in%20labor%20market%20conditions%20is%20unmistakable%2C%26quot%3B%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fstocks%2Fstock-market-today-investors-await-jerome-powells-jackson-hole-speech-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPowell%20said%20in%20a%20speech%20in%20Jackson%20Hole%2C%20Wyoming%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20on%20Friday%2C%20adding%2C%20%26quot%3BWe%20do%20not%20seek%20or%20welcome%20further%20cooling%20in%20labor%20market%20conditions.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELabor%20market%20data%20in%20the%20months%20ahead%20will%20show%20whether%20or%20not%20the%20Fed's%20soft-landing%20goal%20is%20in%20view.%20If%20further%20weakening%20emerges%2C%20as%20Rosenberg%20expects%2C%20investors%20could%20be%20in%20for%20a%20bumpy%20rest%20of%20the%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstock-market-crash-recession-labor-market-revisions-rate-cuts-rosenberg-2024-8%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1724490002000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F661030981caec1275a6d4eea%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22http