20they%20start%20understanding%20the%20world%20and%20environment%20around%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIn%20the%20first%20few%20years%20of%20life%2C%20especially%20the%20first%20six%20months%2C%20a%20child%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20know%20how%20to%20ask%20for%20something.%20The%20presence%20of%20a%20parent%20to%20comfort%20them%20makes%20the%20child%20feel%20safe%20and%20creates%20a%20secure%20attachment%20style.%20This%20ensures%20that%20the%20child%20starts%20trusting%20his%20or%20her%20environment%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Suman.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAdding%20to%20this%2C%20Harpreet%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CParenting%20is%20not%20about%20the%20child%2C%20it%20is%20about%20the%20parent.%20Having%20a%20child%20gives%20us%20a%20window%20of%20opportunity%20to%20genuinely%20reflect%20and%20change%20ourselves.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20Harpreet%20started%20enjoying%20being%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F349527%2Fnew-mothers-online-support-groups-postpartum-breastfeeding-formula-sleep-training-parenting%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehands-on%20father%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20he%20had%20a%20blast%20with%20his%20daughter.%20He%20would%20take%20her%20to%20the%20park%2C%20the%20swimming%20pool%20and%20just%20enjoyed%20being%20a%20parent.%20This%20allowed%20him%20to%20notice%20how%20other%20children%20interacted%20with%20their%20parents.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CTake%20an%20example%20of%20a%20swimming%20class.%20Despite%20some%20children%E2%80%99s%20fear%2C%20the%20instructor%20simply%20throws%20the%20child%20in%20the%20water.%20But%20how%20does%20it%20impact%20the%20child%3F%20Does%20this%20adversely%20affect%20them%3F%20Why%20does%20a%20parent%20allow%20this%3F%20I%20had%20so%20many%20questions%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20shares.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20became%20clear%20to%20him%20that%20the%20blueprint%20of%20a%20well-adjusted%20human%20being%20is%20laid%20out%20in%20the%20early%20years.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-quote%20wp-block-quote-is-layout-flow%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20first%20six%20to%20eight%20years%20of%20our%20lives%20matter%20the%20most%20as%20the%20first%20%E2%80%98AI%20model%E2%80%99%20of%20our%20brain%20is%20written%20without%20our%20consent.%20Children%20just%20become%20what%20they%20see%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20adds%20emphatically.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20then%20started%20sharing%20his%20understanding%20of%20parenting%20on%20social%20media%20and%20why%20children%20behave%20a%20certain%20way.%20With%20parents%20leading%20busy%20lives%2C%20Harpreet%20wishes%20to%20help%20them%20through%20his%20five-minute%20videos.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98Parents%2C%20observe%20from%20a%20distance%E2%80%99%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CChildren%20don%E2%80%99t%20come%20with%20a%20manual.%20Earlier%2C%20people%20would%20say%2C%20%3Cem%3E%E2%80%98Bacche%20aise%20hi%20bade%20ho%20jayenge%E2%80%99%20%3C%2Fem%3E(%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F333887%2Fsangopita-shelter-home-disabled-children-cerebral-palsy-autism-adhd%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EChildren%20grow%20up%20automatically%3C%2Fa%3E).%20Yes%2C%20but%20will%20they%20grow%20up%20properly%3F%20That%20is%20why%20I%20want%20parents%20to%20observe%20their%20children.%20Think%20about%20%3Cem%3Ewhy%20%3C%2Fem%3Ethey%20are%20doing%20what%20they%20are%20doing%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20830px)%20100vw%2C%20830px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F08%2FWhatsApp-Image-2024-08-20-at-14.20.59-1724423013.jpeg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22830%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Harpreet%20found%20his%20calling%20after%2040%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fupl